<body>
<p>
<div>
<p align="center">Vaccination schedule from birth to 6 months (180 days) old.<sup>(1),(2),(3)</sup></p>
<form name="immcalc" tal:attributes="action python:view.url('immcalc')" method="POST">
<br />
Date of Exam: <input type="text" name="examdate" value="1900/01/01" size="10" maxlength="10" />
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Date of Birth: <input type="text" name="dob" value="1900/01/01" size="10" maxlength="10" />
&nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="font-size: smaller;"><em>Dates must be in the format:</em> YYYY/MM/DD</span>
<br /><br />

2) Vaccination types:<span style="font-size: smaller;"><em>Enter the number (0-3) in the boxes of the immunizations that the child has already  received.</em></span><br />

<table>
<th>Immunization Name</th>&nbsp;<th>Number of Doses Already Given</th>
<tr><td align="center">Hepatitis B<td align="center"><input type="text" name="hepatitisB" value="0" size="1" maxlength="1" /></td></tr>

<tr><td align="center">tetravalent (DTP+Hib)</td><td align="center"><input type="text" name="tetravalent" value="0" size="1" maxlength="1" /></td></tr>

<tr><td align="center">Polio</td><td align="center"><input type="text" name="polio" value="0" size="1" maxlength="1" /></td></tr>

<tr><td align="center">Rotavirus</td><td align="center"><input type="text" name="rotavirus" value="0" size="1" maxlength="1" /></td></tr>
</table>

<br /><button name="calc" type="submit">Submit</button>
</form>
</div>
<hr />
<p>
<i>Footnotes:</i><br />
<span style="font-size: smaller;">(1) The decision rules are based on WHO recommendations and may vary from country to country and within regions of the same country depending on national and local vaccination policies.<br /> 
(2) Based on WHO recommendations found on WHO and other related websites on July 7th, 2009 and subjected to change at any time.<br />
(3) This demo is supposed to act as a technical example of the implementation of decision support systems using OSHIP and should never be used as a decision-making tool for the vaccination recommendation of real cases.</span>
</p>

